OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FThe schools watchdog's latest warnings
OL,7,Fon literacy in Wales will sound
OL,8,Ffamiliar to many.
OL,10,FEstyn's Chief Inspector says standards
OL,11,Fare too variable in schools and,
OL,12,Fremarkably, that the literacy skills
OL,13,Fof too many of the teachers themselves
OL,14,Fare weak. This is perhaps unsurprising
OL,15,Fwhen the report also claims that
OL,16,Funiversities are rarely equipping
OL,17,Fstudent teachers with the knowledge
OL,18,Fneeded of how to teach reading well.
OL,20,FBut one line in today's report stands
OL,21,Fout.
