OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FEstyn says some primary schools are
OL,7,F"placing disproportionate emphasis on
OL,8,Fdecoding or technical accuracy at the
OL,9,Fexpense of deeper comprehension and
OL,10,Freader engagement".
OL,12,FThat is a bold claim.
OL,14,FIn plain English, decoding is the
OL,15,Fability to read words by linking
OL,16,Fletters to the sounds they make.
OL,17,FComprehension is understanding and
OL,18,Fmaking meaning from text.
