OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FA large body of international
OL,7,Fscientific evidence shows that
OL,8,Fdecoding is a critical foundation of
OL,9,Freading development. Children who
OL,10,Fcannot do this fluently tend to
OL,11,Fstruggle to understand what they read,
OL,12,Fregardless of the comprehension
OL,13,Fstrategies they are taught.
OL,15,FThat is why warnings about focusing
OL,16,F"too much" on decoding will raise
OL,17,Feyebrows among literacy specialists -
OL,18,Fparticularly in a country where
OL,19,Freading outcomes remain so weak and
OL,20,Fthe national evidence base is
OL,21,Fvirtually non-existent.
