OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FThe "personalised assessments" taken
OL,7,Fby all pupils are not designed to test
OL,8,Fearly decoding skills but rather focus
OL,9,Fon comprehension. Pupils also do not
OL,10,Fanswer the same questions, making
OL,11,Fmeaningful Wales-wide comparisons
OL,12,Fdifficult.
OL,14,FThe Welsh government also avoids
OL,15,Fprescribing how reading should be
OL,16,Ftaught, or how schools should measure
OL,17,Fearly progress.
