OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FToday's report repeatedly calls for
OL,7,F"balance" between decoding,
OL,8,Fcomprehension and enjoyment of
OL,9,Freading. In theory, that sounds
OL,10,Fappealing.
OL,12,FThe difficulty is that reading does
OL,13,Fnot develop evenly across these areas.
OL,14,FScientific research consistently shows
OL,15,Fthat fluent comprehension depends on
OL,16,Faccurate, automatic word reading.
OL,17,FChildren need to decode confidently
OL,18,Fbefore they can read fluently.
