OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FWales is trying to improve how reading
OL,7,Fis taught without the basic evidence
OL,8,Fneeded to do so with confidence. The
OL,9,Fcurriculum provides limited guidance,
OL,10,Fand Estyn inspects against that
OL,11,Fvagueness.
OL,13,FThat gives the watchdog extraordinary
OL,14,Finfluence to shape classroom practice
OL,15,Fthrough inspection language with a
OL,16,Fquestionable evidence base and without
OL,17,Fany measurable outcomes.
