OL,3,CWales's reading problem ` and the data
OL,4,Cgap behind it
OL,6,FThe education secretary, Lynne Neagle,
OL,7,Flast year announced Wales would take
OL,8,Fpart in the international reading test
OL,9,Ffor 10-year-olds known as PIRLS. But
OL,10,Fthe first results aren't expected
OL,11,Funtil the end of 2027.
OL,13,FBefore Wales can fix its reading
OL,14,Fproblem, it needs to address its
OL,15,Fevidence and accountability problem.
OL,16,FUntil it does, recommendations to
OL,17,Fschools risk being little more than
OL,18,Fguesswork.
